<li>Samuel Bowles &amp; <a href="/wiki/Herbert_Gintis" title="Herbert Gintis">Herbert Gintis</a> (1975). "The Problem with Human Capital Theory--A Marxian Critique," <i>American Economic Review</i>, 65(2), pp. 74-82,</li>
<li>Sherwin Rosen (1987). "Human capital," <a href="/wiki/The_New_Palgrave:_A_Dictionary_of_Economics" title="The New Palgrave: A Dictionary of Economics">The New Palgrave: A Dictionary of Economics</a>, v. 2, pp. 681-90.</li>
<li>Seymour W. Itzkoff (2003). <i>Intellectual Capital in Twenty-First-Century Politics</i>. Ashfield, MA: Paideia, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0913993204" class="internal">ISBN 0-913993-20-4</a></li>
<li>Brian Keeley (2007). <i>OECD Insights; Human Capital</i>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9264029087" class="internal">ISBN 92-64-02908-7</a> <a href="http://www.oecd.org/insights/humancapital" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.oecd.org/insights/humancapital" rel="nofollow">[3]</a></li>
</ul>
